Одним з головних показників, які я буду використовувати на більшості візуалізаціях - це Good Sleep Rate¶

Він розраховується як частка людей, які сплять >= 7 годин на добу з усієї групи¶

# x.rfseat2
seatbelt_replace = {1: 'Always wears seatbelt', 2: 'Sometimes wear seatbelt', 9: np.nan}

# x.incomg
income_replace = {1:'<15k', 2:'15k-25k', 3:'25k-35k', 4:'35k-50k', 5:'>50k', 9:np.nan}

# x.raceprv
race_replace = {1:'white', 2:'black', 3:'native american', 4:'asian', 5:'pacific islander', 6:'other', 7:'multiracial', 8:'hispanic'}

# x.sex
sex_replace = {1:'male', 2:'female'}

# x.ageg5yr
age_replace = {1:'18-24', 2:'25-29', 3:'30-34', 4:'35-39', 5:'40-44', 6:'45-49', 7:'50-54', 8:'55-59', 9:'60-64', 10:'65-69', 11:'70-74', 12:'75-79', 13:'80+', 14:np.nan}

# genhlth
genhlth_replace = {1: 'Excellent', 2: 'Very good', 3: 'Good', 4: 'Fair', 5: 'Poor', 7: np.nan, 9: np.nan}

# marital
marital_replace = {1: 'Married', 2: 'Divorced', 3: 'Widowed', 4: 'Separated', 5: 'Never married', 6: ' A member of an unmarried couple', 9: 'Refused'}

# x.bmi5cat
bmi5cat_replace = {1: 'Underweight', 2: 'Normal Weight', 3: 'Overweight', 4: 'Obese'}

# x.smoker3
smoke_replace = {1: 'Active Smoker', 2: 'Smokes sometimes', 3: 'Former smoker', 4: 'Never smoked', 9: np.nan}

# x.totinda
employ_replace = {1: 'Employed for wages', 2: 'Self-employed', 3: 'Out of work > 1 year', 4: 'Out of work for < 1 year', 5: 'Homemaker', 6: 'Student', 7: 'Retired', 8: 'Unable to work', 9: np.nan}

# x.educag
education_replace = {1: 'Didn\'t graduate School', 2: 'Graduated School', 3: 'Attended College or Technical School', 4: 'Graduated from College or Technical School', 9: np.nan}

df = pd.read_csv('LLCP2020.csv')
df = df[cols]
In [5]:
df['x.rfseat2'].replace(seatbelt_replace, inplace = True)

df['x.incomg'].replace(income_replace, inplace = True)

df['x.raceprv'].replace(race_replace, inplace = True)

df['x.sex'].replace(sex_replace, inplace = True)

df['x.ageg5yr'].replace(age_replace, inplace = True)

df['genhlth'].replace(genhlth_replace, inplace = True)

df['marital'].replace(marital_replace, inplace = True)

df['x.bmi5cat'].replace(bmi5cat_replace, inplace = True)

df['x.smoker3'].replace(smoke_replace, inplace = True)

df['x.totinda'].replace(employ_replace, inplace = True)

df['x.educag'].replace(education_replace, inplace = True)

# Good Sleep Rate
df['sleep_enough'] = (df['sleptim1'] > 7)*1

df = df.rename(columns={'x.state': 'state'
                  ,'x.raceprv': 'race'
                  ,'x.ageg5yr': 'age'
                  ,'x.sex': 'sex'
                  ,'x.educag': 'education'
                  ,'x.bmi5cat': 'bmi'
                  ,'x.totinda': 'income'
                  ,'x.smoker3': 'smoker'
                  ,'x.rfseat2': 'seat_belt'})

health_groups = df.groupby(['genhlth']).agg({'sleep_enough':'mean', 'state': 'count'})
health_groups_lbl = ['Poor', 'Fair', 'Good', 'Very good', 'Excellent']

health_groups = health_groups.reindex(index = health_groups_lbl)

In [8]:
_ = plt.bar(health_groups.index, health_groups['sleep_enough']*100)
_ = plt.xlabel('Self-Evaluated Health State', fontsize=15)
_ = plt.ylabel('Good Sleep Rate, %', fontsize=15)
_ = plt.title('% of people with average sleep time >= 7 hours by self-evaluated health state', fontsize=20)
_ = plt.ylim(0, 55)
_ = plt.xticks(weight='bold')
_ = plt.yticks(size = 13)

for x,y in zip(health_groups.index, health_groups['sleep_enough']*100):
    u = str(health_groups['sleep_enough'].loc[x])
    label = '{:.1f}%'.format(y)
    
    plt.annotate(label, (x,y), textcoords='offset points', xytext=(0, 13), ha='center', fontsize=15, fontweight='bold')

plt.show()
In [9]:
health_educ_groups = df.groupby(['genhlth', 'education'])['state'].count().astype('float')
for g in health_groups_lbl:
    sub_total = health_educ_groups[g].sum()
    for i in health_educ_groups[g].index:
        health_educ_groups[g][i] /= sub_total
        
health_educ_groups = health_educ_groups.unstack(level=1).reindex(index = health_groups_lbl)*100
health_educ_groups.columns = ["Didn't graduate School",'Graduated School'
                              ,'Attended College or Technical School', 'Graduated from College or Technical School']

In [13]:
bmi_smoke_groups = df.groupby(['bmi', 'smoker']
          ).agg({'sleep_enough': 'mean'
                 ,'state':'count'}
          ).rename(columns={'sleep_enough': 'sleep_rate'
                            ,'state':'group_size'}
          )

bmi_ordered = ['Underweight', 'Normal Weight', 'Overweight', 'Obese']
smoke_ordered = ['Active Smoker', 'Smokes sometimes', 'Former smoker', 'Never smoked']

bmi_smoke_groups = bmi_smoke_groups.reindex(bmi_ordered, level=0)
bmi_smoke_groups = bmi_smoke_groups.reindex(smoke_ordered, level=1)

bmi_smoke_groups = bmi_smoke_groups.reset_index(drop=False, inplace = False)
bmi_smoke_groups['sleep_rate'] = np.round(bmi_smoke_groups['sleep_rate']*100, 2)

alt.Chart(bmi_smoke_groups
         ,title = 'Good Sleep Rate by BMI and Smoke addiction'
        ).mark_point(filled = True
        ).encode(
             x = alt.X('bmi:N'
                      ,sort=bmi_ordered[::-1]
                      ,axis = alt.Axis(
                                       labelAngle = 0
                                      ,labelFontSize = 12
                                      ,title = 'Body Mass Index Category')
                      )
            ,y = alt.Y('smoker:N'
                      ,sort=smoke_ordered[::-1]
                      ,axis = alt.Axis(
                                        labelFontSize = 12)
                                       ,title = 'Type of Smokers')
            ,color = alt.Color('sleep_rate:Q'
                              ,scale = alt.Scale(scheme = 'redyellowgreen')
                              ,title = 'Good Sleep Rate, %')
            ,size = alt.value(5000)
#             ,size = alt.Size('group_size:Q'
#                              ,scale = alt.Scale(range = [100, 10000])
#                              ,title = 'Number of Respondents')
            ,tooltip = [
                     alt.Tooltip('sleep_rate:Q', title = 'Good Sleep Rate')
                    ,alt.Tooltip('group_size:Q', title = 'Number of Respondents')
                    ]
        ).properties(width = 660, height = 480
        ).configure_axis(
             titleFontSize=14
        ).configure_title(fontSize=20)

alt.Chart(us
         ,title = 'Share of people with enough amount of sleep by state').transform_lookup(
     lookup = 'state'
    ,from_ = alt.LookupData(data = state_groups
                           ,key = 'state'
                           ,fields=['sleep_rate', 'state_size'])
    ).mark_geoshape(stroke = 'white'
                   ,strokeWidth = 1
    ).encode(
        color = alt.Color('sleep_rate:Q'
                          ,title = 'Good Sleep Rate, %'
                          ,scale = alt.Scale(scheme = 'redyellowgreen')),
        tooltip = [
             alt.Tooltip('NAME:N', title = 'State')
            ,alt.Tooltip('state_size:N', title = 'Number of Respondents')
            ,alt.Tooltip('sleep_rate:Q', title = 'Good Sleep Rate, %')
        ]
    ).properties(width = 815, height = 720
    ).configure_view(strokeWidth = 0
    ).configure_title(
                fontSize=20
           )
